1
00:01:41,130 --> 00:01:45,890
[Justifiable Defense]

2
00:01:46,039 --> 00:01:48,970
[Episode 14]

3
00:01:51,039 --> 00:01:52,759
Duan Hongshan used to say this often:

4
00:01:52,759 --> 00:01:54,960
Put yourself in the defendant's shoes.

5
00:01:55,070 --> 00:01:56,150
Easy to say,

6
00:01:56,789 --> 00:01:57,680
but hard

7
00:01:58,759 --> 00:01:59,960
to actually achieve.

8
00:02:00,510 --> 00:02:02,350
Li, be honest with me,

9
00:02:02,760 --> 00:02:04,920
based on what you know
about Duan Hongshan,

10
00:02:04,920 --> 00:02:06,480
do you truly believe

11
00:02:06,480 --> 00:02:08,539
what he did was justifiable defense?

12
00:02:08,630 --> 00:02:11,080
Or are you just following
procedural justice?

13
00:02:11,080 --> 00:02:12,590
Can't we give Duan Hongshan

14
00:02:12,590 --> 00:02:13,850
substantive justice?

15
00:02:14,150 --> 00:02:15,550
We're not philosophers.

16
00:02:15,750 --> 00:02:17,360
The legal facts we establish

17
00:02:17,560 --> 00:02:18,870
must be based on evidence.

18
00:02:18,870 --> 00:02:20,130
If there's no evidence

19
00:02:20,310 --> 00:02:23,000
to prove Duan Hongshan
acted in justifiable defense,

20
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:24,060
then it's illegal.

21
00:02:24,470 --> 00:02:25,800
The public will see this

22
00:02:26,280 --> 00:02:28,280
as officials protecting their own.

23
00:02:28,520 --> 00:02:29,360
It seems

24
00:02:30,360 --> 00:02:33,079
our belief in Duan Hongshan's
justifiable defense

25
00:02:33,079 --> 00:02:35,210
will have to remain just in our hearts.

26
00:02:36,340 --> 00:02:36,680
[Procuratorial Hearing]

27
00:02:36,680 --> 00:02:38,310
In your previous cases,

28
00:02:38,430 --> 00:02:40,710
you've ruled excessive defense

29
00:02:40,870 --> 00:02:42,470
or manslaughter for others.

30
00:02:42,710 --> 00:02:44,470
Did you consider these factors then?

31
00:02:44,470 --> 00:02:45,470
I did.

32
00:02:46,150 --> 00:02:48,350
Put yourself in the defendant's shoes.

33
00:02:49,079 --> 00:02:50,800
That is what the procuratorate

34
00:02:50,800 --> 00:02:52,560
requires of every prosecutor

35
00:02:53,310 --> 00:02:55,000
when handling

36
00:02:55,000 --> 00:02:55,960
each case.

37
00:02:57,400 --> 00:02:59,329
I used to think I had achieved that:

38
00:02:59,680 --> 00:02:59,800
[Procuratorial Hearing]

39
00:02:59,800 --> 00:03:01,280
we gathered together

40
00:03:02,280 --> 00:03:03,680
to carefully deliberate

41
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:05,060
and to pool wisdom,

42
00:03:05,750 --> 00:03:08,030
putting ourselves in the parties' position

43
00:03:08,030 --> 00:03:09,630
to analyze the entire case.

44
00:03:10,630 --> 00:03:12,190
But today I realized

45
00:03:14,910 --> 00:03:16,510
I never truly achieved that.

46
00:03:18,710 --> 00:03:20,770
And I couldn't possibly have done so.

47
00:03:21,800 --> 00:03:23,260
Because only when I myself

48
00:03:24,030 --> 00:03:26,360
are truly in such a desperate situation,

49
00:03:28,310 --> 00:03:30,960
with a gleaming knife
right before my eyes,

50
00:03:32,030 --> 00:03:33,490
can I truly understand it.

51
00:03:34,520 --> 00:03:35,590
At that moment,

52
00:03:37,560 --> 00:03:39,590
I couldn't take out my phone

53
00:03:39,870 --> 00:03:41,750
to record videos as evidence.

54
00:03:42,750 --> 00:03:44,910
Nor could I calmly consider

55
00:03:45,120 --> 00:03:46,780
whether my defensive actions

56
00:03:47,030 --> 00:03:48,520
might cause

57
00:03:48,520 --> 00:03:49,800
fatal harm to the attacker.

58
00:03:49,800 --> 00:03:52,600
But Duan Hongshan, you
are a prosecutor after all!

59
00:03:57,960 --> 00:04:00,030
I want to ask everyone here.

60
00:04:00,520 --> 00:04:01,680
In your eyes,

61
00:04:02,080 --> 00:04:04,190
what exactly is a prosecutor?

62
00:04:04,330 --> 00:04:05,150
[Prosecutor]

63
00:04:05,150 --> 00:04:07,840
Is a prosecutor a specific individual,

64
00:04:08,080 --> 00:04:09,840
or just an abstract concept?

65
00:04:10,140 --> 00:04:10,630
[Procuratorial Hearing]

66
00:04:10,630 --> 00:04:11,800
If you consider them human beings,

67
00:04:11,800 --> 00:04:13,710
they can't be flawless

68
00:04:14,270 --> 00:04:16,480
or unchanging forever.

69
00:04:17,430 --> 00:04:19,070
We can't expect someone

70
00:04:19,600 --> 00:04:21,329
to never make mistakes, can we?

71
00:04:21,480 --> 00:04:23,950
A life for a life is natural justice.

72
00:04:23,950 --> 00:04:26,270
No matter what you say, I can't accept it.

73
00:04:26,750 --> 00:04:28,610
Just on Director Duan's word alone,

74
00:04:28,610 --> 00:04:29,000
[Hearing Officer]

75
00:04:29,000 --> 00:04:30,660
that person died for nothing?

76
00:04:31,040 --> 00:04:32,640
This doesn't make any sense.

77
00:04:32,720 --> 00:04:34,600
The public won't understand either, right?

78
00:04:34,600 --> 00:04:36,430
Don't tell me the law

79
00:04:36,830 --> 00:04:39,240
is whatever the procuratorate says it is?

80
00:04:39,560 --> 00:04:40,600
Exactly!

81
00:04:40,830 --> 00:04:42,750
No matter how sophisticated the law is,

82
00:04:42,750 --> 00:04:44,350
it still needs to give people

83
00:04:44,390 --> 00:04:46,630
a basic understanding, right?

84
00:04:49,870 --> 00:04:50,560
Everyone.

85
00:04:51,210 --> 00:04:52,120
[To Prosecutor Gong]

86
00:04:52,120 --> 00:04:52,870
This

87
00:04:53,220 --> 00:04:56,040
is Duan Hongshan's
previous resignation letter.

88
00:04:56,040 --> 00:04:56,750
[Hearing Officer]

89
00:04:56,750 --> 00:04:59,680
In this case, Duan Hongshan

90
00:04:59,800 --> 00:05:02,630
wanted to separate himself
from his professional identity.

91
00:05:02,630 --> 00:05:03,480
See that?

92
00:05:03,750 --> 00:05:05,720
When trouble comes,
he thinks about resigning,

93
00:05:05,720 --> 00:05:06,870
as if it would make everything okay!

94
00:05:06,870 --> 00:05:07,680
Exactly!

95
00:05:08,480 --> 00:05:09,800
Our judicial authorities

96
00:05:09,800 --> 00:05:12,430
won't allow Duan Hongshan to resign now.

97
00:05:13,120 --> 00:05:15,360
Because the Criminal Law clearly states

98
00:05:15,360 --> 00:05:17,160
that the status of judicial personnel

99
00:05:17,160 --> 00:05:20,890
is considered an aggravating factor
in certain legal provisions.

100
00:05:25,850 --> 00:05:27,630
[Prosecutor]

101
00:05:27,630 --> 00:05:28,430
Now,

102
00:05:29,560 --> 00:05:30,600
please listen to

103
00:05:30,600 --> 00:05:33,000
Suspect Duan Hongshan's final statement.

104
00:05:44,950 --> 00:05:46,040
A life for a life.

105
00:05:47,560 --> 00:05:48,680
Respect the dead.

106
00:05:48,710 --> 00:05:49,870
[Uphold Virtue, Respect the Law, Stay Just, and Strive Forward]

107
00:05:49,870 --> 00:05:51,430
These are thought patterns

108
00:05:52,870 --> 00:05:55,870
that have formed in our minds
over thousands of years.

109
00:05:56,430 --> 00:05:58,070
This mindset deeply influences

110
00:05:58,070 --> 00:05:59,530
every one of us here today.

111
00:06:00,160 --> 00:06:01,430
We all believe

112
00:06:02,920 --> 00:06:05,250
that the deceased deserves our sympathy.

113
00:06:05,310 --> 00:06:07,360
We also hope that the law

114
00:06:08,190 --> 00:06:09,600
can severely punish

115
00:06:09,600 --> 00:06:10,950
the killer.

116
00:06:11,870 --> 00:06:13,160
But the reality is,

117
00:06:14,430 --> 00:06:16,040
in cases like this,

118
00:06:17,270 --> 00:06:18,600
the true victim

119
00:06:20,430 --> 00:06:22,760
is the person
who fights back with a knife.

120
00:06:39,830 --> 00:06:41,120
I'm not optimistic

121
00:06:41,120 --> 00:06:42,450
about my outcome today.

122
00:06:43,950 --> 00:06:44,680
But I hope

123
00:06:44,680 --> 00:06:46,560
that through my case,

124
00:06:47,870 --> 00:06:49,159
more people will

125
00:06:49,870 --> 00:06:51,670
gain a clearer understanding of

126
00:06:51,750 --> 00:06:54,280
the legal provision
of justifiable defense.

127
00:06:55,800 --> 00:06:57,310
I also hope our prosecution system

128
00:06:57,310 --> 00:06:58,390
will realize

129
00:06:58,750 --> 00:07:00,430
that our standards for judging

130
00:07:00,430 --> 00:07:01,630
justifiable defense

131
00:07:02,750 --> 00:07:04,040
have been too harsh.

132
00:07:04,680 --> 00:07:05,920
Since we cannot expect

133
00:07:05,920 --> 00:07:07,510
a victim to be perfect.

134
00:07:09,480 --> 00:07:10,720
We must also accept

135
00:07:11,310 --> 00:07:13,070
the choices they make

136
00:07:14,430 --> 00:07:16,290
when their lives are threatened.

137
00:07:17,600 --> 00:07:20,200
I firmly believe
justice exists in this world.

138
00:07:21,190 --> 00:07:22,720
However, absolute justice

139
00:07:24,040 --> 00:07:25,600
is like a perfect circle.

140
00:07:28,720 --> 00:07:30,240
People can never draw

141
00:07:30,240 --> 00:07:31,240
a perfect circle.

142
00:07:32,310 --> 00:07:33,830
Does that mean we can say

143
00:07:33,830 --> 00:07:36,230
perfect circles don't exist in this world?

144
00:07:36,830 --> 00:07:37,630
They do exist,

145
00:07:38,560 --> 00:07:40,310
but only in concept.

146
00:07:41,920 --> 00:07:43,070
Absolute justice

147
00:07:44,120 --> 00:07:46,190
also exists only in concept.

148
00:07:49,680 --> 00:07:51,040
In our legal system,

149
00:07:52,120 --> 00:07:53,390
justice is relative.

150
00:07:55,270 --> 00:07:56,950
Or we could say it's flawed.

151
00:07:58,190 --> 00:07:59,630
The law defines

152
00:08:00,800 --> 00:08:02,530
how we should achieve justice.

153
00:08:02,920 --> 00:08:04,430
If we don't follow the law,

154
00:08:05,510 --> 00:08:08,510
and only follow our own
understanding of justice...

155
00:08:09,750 --> 00:08:11,270
Kill a man within ten paces;

156
00:08:11,270 --> 00:08:12,800
leave no trace for a thousand miles.

157
00:08:12,800 --> 00:08:13,800
When it's done, dust off and depart,

158
00:08:13,800 --> 00:08:15,430
hiding both achievement and fame.

159
00:08:15,430 --> 00:08:17,160
It sounds exhilarating,

160
00:08:17,480 --> 00:08:19,630
but this way of achieving justice

161
00:08:21,040 --> 00:08:22,920
will bring greater injustice.

162
00:08:24,430 --> 00:08:25,920
As the saying goes,

163
00:08:27,040 --> 00:08:28,720
it is our good intentions

164
00:08:31,000 --> 00:08:33,200
that drag people into earthly hell.

165
00:08:35,270 --> 00:08:37,200
Today, facing my own case,

166
00:08:41,030 --> 00:08:43,890
I acknowledge the justice
of judicial procedures.

167
00:08:47,030 --> 00:08:49,120
I also accept justice with flaws.

168
00:09:08,870 --> 00:09:10,330
Allow me to say a few words.

169
00:09:13,240 --> 00:09:15,320
Light is visible

170
00:09:16,230 --> 00:09:18,890
because someone shields you
from the darkness.

171
00:09:19,030 --> 00:09:22,090
As a prosecutor who should be
at the prosecutor's bench

172
00:09:22,120 --> 00:09:23,200
to defend the law

173
00:09:23,720 --> 00:09:25,480
and pursue justice,

174
00:09:26,320 --> 00:09:27,030
now,

175
00:09:27,600 --> 00:09:28,860
he sits there instead.

176
00:09:29,840 --> 00:09:31,670
Duan Hongshan once shielded many people

177
00:09:31,670 --> 00:09:32,840
from darkness,

178
00:09:32,870 --> 00:09:35,200
but now he cannot bring light to himself.

179
00:09:35,630 --> 00:09:36,670
Twenty years ago,

180
00:09:36,840 --> 00:09:38,600
he chose to believe in the law

181
00:09:38,790 --> 00:09:40,150
and face darkness head-on.

182
00:09:40,150 --> 00:09:41,080
But now,

183
00:09:41,240 --> 00:09:43,240
because of that choice,

184
00:09:43,630 --> 00:09:45,960
he faces an even harsher moral judgment.

185
00:09:45,960 --> 00:09:46,910
Is this situation

186
00:09:46,910 --> 00:09:49,120
fair to Duan Hongshan?

187
00:09:49,600 --> 00:09:50,550
Is it just?

188
00:09:51,120 --> 00:09:52,360
Is this justice?

189
00:10:00,150 --> 00:10:01,200
A prosecutor

190
00:10:01,670 --> 00:10:04,200
is not only the pursuer of criminals,

191
00:10:04,390 --> 00:10:06,590
but also the protector of the innocent.

192
00:10:10,000 --> 00:10:11,910
We should punish crime,

193
00:10:12,150 --> 00:10:13,810
but what we should do even more

194
00:10:13,870 --> 00:10:15,150
is to speak up for the weak

195
00:10:15,150 --> 00:10:16,600
and plead for the people.

196
00:10:16,790 --> 00:10:18,360
So, whoever sits here,

197
00:10:18,360 --> 00:10:19,480
no matter who he is

198
00:10:19,480 --> 00:10:20,960
or what his status may be,

199
00:10:20,960 --> 00:10:22,240
we should give him

200
00:10:22,240 --> 00:10:23,790
the most fair judgment.

201
00:10:25,720 --> 00:10:26,440
Because

202
00:10:27,840 --> 00:10:30,790
the law must not yield to wrongdoing.

203
00:10:32,910 --> 00:10:33,910
And also because…

204
00:10:38,390 --> 00:10:40,200
someone once told me:

205
00:10:41,840 --> 00:10:43,970
It's not the cases that we're handing,

206
00:10:44,790 --> 00:10:46,030
but people's lives.

207
00:10:55,910 --> 00:10:56,630
Here,

208
00:10:57,550 --> 00:10:59,120
as a prosecutor,

209
00:10:59,840 --> 00:11:00,630
I promise

210
00:11:01,150 --> 00:11:04,200
I won't stop pursuing the truth
about that day.

211
00:11:09,670 --> 00:11:11,910
Frontline prosecutors don't have it easy.

212
00:11:11,910 --> 00:11:12,670
Indeed.

213
00:11:42,150 --> 00:11:43,150
Prosecutor Gong,

214
00:11:43,200 --> 00:11:44,530
what are you looking at?

215
00:11:46,200 --> 00:11:47,200
I'm watching

216
00:11:47,630 --> 00:11:49,440
birds flying in the rain.

217
00:11:53,910 --> 00:11:55,570
After the hearing procedure,

218
00:11:56,080 --> 00:11:58,000
the hearing officers unanimously believe

219
00:11:58,000 --> 00:11:59,270
there is no evidence to prove

220
00:11:59,270 --> 00:12:01,870
that Duan Hongshan's actions
were defensive,

221
00:12:02,080 --> 00:12:04,080
and thus should be deemed criminal.

222
00:12:13,150 --> 00:12:14,110
Today's hearing

223
00:12:14,200 --> 00:12:14,510
will be…

224
00:12:14,510 --> 00:12:15,150
Wait!

225
00:12:17,840 --> 00:12:19,000
In the cloud storage,

226
00:12:19,000 --> 00:12:19,930
there's a video.

227
00:12:20,320 --> 00:12:21,480
There's a video?

228
00:12:29,790 --> 00:12:31,120
I have thought about it—

229
00:12:31,320 --> 00:12:32,720
if Zhou Delong's phone

230
00:12:32,720 --> 00:12:34,240
had cloud storage activated,

231
00:12:34,240 --> 00:12:35,200
then perhaps

232
00:12:35,200 --> 00:12:37,200
we could find video evidence there.

233
00:12:37,480 --> 00:12:38,360
But we looked,

234
00:12:38,360 --> 00:12:39,550
and there was nothing.

235
00:12:39,550 --> 00:12:41,150
Before the hearing began,

236
00:12:41,200 --> 00:12:43,270
the clerk Ding Yi's words

237
00:12:43,720 --> 00:12:45,180
gave me a new perspective.

238
00:12:45,910 --> 00:12:47,120
I asked the clerks to check,

239
00:12:47,120 --> 00:12:48,380
and now we've found it.

240
00:12:48,870 --> 00:12:51,270
Let's watch the truth
of that day together.

241
00:12:51,750 --> 00:12:53,550
This is the cloud storage
Zhou Delong registered

242
00:12:53,550 --> 00:12:54,350
with Zhou Lin's phone.

243
00:12:54,350 --> 00:12:58,190
[Streaming]

244
00:13:02,930 --> 00:13:07,150
[Streaming]

245
00:13:09,780 --> 00:13:12,640
[Streaming]

246
00:13:15,450 --> 00:13:19,070
[Streaming]

247
00:13:23,080 --> 00:13:24,440
Still trying to run?

248
00:13:27,240 --> 00:13:28,030
Run!

249
00:13:29,550 --> 00:13:30,600
Go ahead, run!

250
00:13:31,480 --> 00:13:33,320
Let's see where you can run to!

251
00:14:19,080 --> 00:14:19,720
♪ The morning breeze blows away worries ♪

252
00:14:19,720 --> 00:14:20,440
Mom,

253
00:14:21,200 --> 00:14:22,400
the rain has stopped.

254
00:14:23,600 --> 00:14:24,440
Yes,

255
00:14:24,870 --> 00:14:26,260
the rain has finally stopped.

256
00:14:26,260 --> 00:14:31,510
♪ Beyond the window waits a cliff ♪

257
00:14:33,110 --> 00:14:39,120
♪ Crossing roads,
finding freedom in the fall ♪

258
00:14:40,300 --> 00:14:46,320
♪ About the dialogue of fate,
I can't tell what I feel ♪

259
00:15:06,030 --> 00:15:07,000
It's time.

260
00:15:08,080 --> 00:15:10,210
It's time to climb up from underwater,

261
00:15:10,630 --> 00:15:12,020
take a good breath,

262
00:15:12,150 --> 00:15:13,480
and see myself clearly.

263
00:15:36,210 --> 00:15:37,710
[Letter of Resignation]

264
00:15:46,720 --> 00:15:48,980
After deliberation during the hearing,

265
00:15:49,720 --> 00:15:52,750
regarding the 4.28 homicide case
at East Suburb Fishery,

266
00:15:52,750 --> 00:15:54,360
The suspect, Duan Hongshan,

267
00:15:54,630 --> 00:15:57,030
is considered to have acted
in justifiable defense

268
00:15:57,030 --> 00:15:59,030
and will not be approved for arrest.

269
00:16:03,720 --> 00:16:06,250
You've finally reached
the exit of this maze.

270
00:16:06,840 --> 00:16:07,900
Are you satisfied?

271
00:16:08,080 --> 00:16:10,120
Your paperwork will be processed soon.

272
00:16:10,120 --> 00:16:11,980
From what little I know about you,

273
00:16:13,440 --> 00:16:15,700
you'd make decisions based on the truth.

274
00:16:16,790 --> 00:16:17,870
Because I know

275
00:16:20,670 --> 00:16:23,130
you want us to see
the other side of the truth.

276
00:16:30,270 --> 00:16:32,390
These days while I was in detention,

277
00:16:34,150 --> 00:16:37,000
I've been trying to think
about everything that happened

278
00:16:37,000 --> 00:16:38,730
from a suspect's perspective.

279
00:16:41,840 --> 00:16:43,640
Only after I figured all this out

280
00:16:45,320 --> 00:16:46,870
did I find out the real motive

281
00:16:46,870 --> 00:16:48,030
of the mastermind.

282
00:16:50,440 --> 00:16:51,630
He wanted to place me

283
00:16:52,750 --> 00:16:54,680
and the entire prosecution system

284
00:16:56,590 --> 00:16:58,390
on opposite sides of the scale.

285
00:17:09,030 --> 00:17:10,030
Actually,

286
00:17:11,750 --> 00:17:13,950
from the moment you turned yourself in,

287
00:17:14,750 --> 00:17:16,510
through your silence,

288
00:17:18,240 --> 00:17:20,030
and up to the point
you dismissed your lawyer,

